            <h1 class="latest-bike-head text-center p-b20">Exploring the Maruti Suzuki Celerio: A Blend of Style, Efficiency, and Innovation</h1>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/march/celerio/fullview.webp" alt="fullview" title="fullview" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>The Maruti Suzuki Celerio has carved a niche for itself in the compact hatchback segment, offering a harmonious blend of contemporary design, fuel efficiency, and innovative features. As a product of Maruti Suzuki, a brand synonymous with reliability and affordability in India, the Celerio stands as a testament to the company's commitment to evolving with modern automotive trends. </p>
            <h3 class="subheading">Sleek and Modern Design</h3>
             <p>The Celerio's exterior showcases a dynamic and youthful appeal. Its sleek contours, expressive front grille, and stylish headlamps contribute to a fresh and modern look. The compact dimensions make it an ideal choice for urban environments, allowing for easy maneuverability and parking. Available in a palette of vibrant colors, including Speedy Blue, Solid Fire Red, and Caffeine Brown, the Celerio caters to diverse aesthetic preferences. </p>
            <h3 class="subheading">Efficient Performance</h3>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/march/celerio/engine.webp" alt="engine" title="engine" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>Under the hood, the Celerio is powered by Maruti's K10C 1.0-liter 3-cylinder petrol engine, delivering 67PS of power and 89Nm of torque. This engine is paired with either a 5-speed manual or an Automated Manual Transmission (AMT), providing flexibility to suit different driving preferences. One of the standout features of the Celerio is its impressive fuel efficiency, with claimed figures reaching up to 26.68 kmpl for the VXi AMT variant, making it one of the most fuel-efficient cars in India. </p>
            <h3 class="subheading">Comfortable and Feature-Rich Interior</h3>
            <p>Step inside the Celerio, and you're greeted with a spacious and thoughtfully designed cabin. The all-black interior exudes a sense of sophistication, while the ergonomic layout ensures a comfortable driving experience. Key interior features include: </p>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/march/celerio/display.webp" alt="display" title="display" /></div>
            </div>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Smartplay Dock with USB, AUX, and Bluetooth Compatibility: </span>Allows seamless connectivity for music and calls. </li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Steering-Mounted Audio Controls: </span> Enhances driving convenience by allowing audio adjustments without taking hands off the wheel. </li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Tilt Steering: </span> Enables drivers to adjust the steering wheel position for optimal comfort. </li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Rear Defogger and Wiper with Washer: </span>Ensures clear visibility during adverse weather conditions.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Additionally, the Celerio offers a generous boot space of 313 liters, accommodating luggage and daily essentials with ease. </p>
            <h3 class="subheading">Safety and Convenience</h3>
            <p>Maruti Suzuki has equipped the Celerio with a host of safety features to ensure peace of mind for both the driver and passengers. Standard safety features across variants include: </p>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/march/celerio/airbags.webp" alt="airbags" title="airbags" /></div>
            </div>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Dual Front Airbags: </span>Provide protection in the event of a frontal collision. </li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) with Electronic Brakeforce Distribution (EBD): </span> Enhances braking stability and control. </li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Hill-Hold Assist (Available in AMT Variants): </span>Prevents the car from rolling back on inclines, adding to driving confidence. </li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine Immobilizer: </span>Offers protection against theft by preventing the engine from starting with an unauthorized key. </li>
            </ul>
            <h3 class="subheading">Variants and Pricing</h3>
            <div class="row m-b20">
                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/valueformoney/2025/march/celerio/side.webp" alt="side" title="side" /></div>
            </div>
            <p>The Celerio is available in four distinct variants, each catering to different customer needs: </p>
            <p><span class="font-weight-700">1.LXi: </span>Priced at ₹5.25 lakh, this base variant offers essential features suitable for budget-conscious buyers. </p>
            <p><span class="font-weight-700">2.VXi: </span>Starting at ₹5.74 lakh for the manual and ₹6.24 lakh for the AMT, the VXi adds conveniences like body-colored ORVMs and door handles, full wheel covers, and power windows. </p>
            <p><span class="font-weight-700">3.ZXi: </span>At ₹5.94 lakh (manual) and ₹6.44 lakh (AMT), the ZXi variant introduces features like a Smartplay Dock audio system, steering-mounted controls, and keyless entry. </p>
            <p><span class="font-weight-700">4.ZXi+:</span> The top-tier variant, priced at ₹6.50 lakh (manual) and ₹7.00 lakh (AMT), boasts additional features such as alloy wheels, fog lamps, a 7-inch touchscreen infotainment system with Apple CarPlay and Android Auto, and push-button start.</p>
